  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across five flow-speed combinations; seven of thirteen credibility factors were formally assessed and the remaining six were flagged as epistemic gaps. The assessment team judged that the Monte Carlo UQ campaign, combined with detailed mesh-refinement studies and software QA documentation, collectively justified a Medium assurance level. NOTE (adversarial): the decision record below records 'Accepted' while multiple assessed factors carry achievedLevel below requiredLevel, including a Discretization error factor at achievedLevel 2 against requiredLevel 4 — a Critical W-AR-02 condition. The Medium assurance declaration is therefore structurally unsupported and fires COMPOUND-03.",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-absolute-index",
